A:

Yes, apple is in the real world.
I am a real person, and I live in London, UK. Apple is available in supermarkets all over the UK. However, some of those supermarkets are in London, so they don't have apples in their shops. The supermarket I mentioned just had apples, but the shops are in another city. To make the story somewhat easier to read, I am referring to the US supermarkets.

When I say that I am talking about it in “real” terms, I am not talking about a single apple. I am talking about the entire tree of apples, and about the apple itself. To be truly precise, I want to consider the tree as a whole, and not just a single apple. It has to be that apple, which is defined by its fruit.

Apple trees produce more apples than are eaten.
